<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-567] Groovy shell swoallows exceptions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-567</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a script throws a run time exception the stack trace is no longer displayed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead you get&lt;br/&gt;
Caught: groovy.lang.GroovyRuntimeException: This script or class could not be run. &lt;br/&gt;
It should either: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;have a main method,&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;be a class extending GroovyTestCase,&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;or implement the Runnable interface.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
