                            <comment id="14460398" author="guillaume" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2004 15:55:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tug, do you have a sample script which could illustrate the problem?&lt;br/&gt;
I tried with the following script:&lt;br/&gt;
-------------&lt;br/&gt;
int a = null&lt;br/&gt;
a.toString()&lt;br/&gt;
-------------&lt;br/&gt;
which should throw a NullPointerException.&lt;br/&gt;
And this RuntimeException is thrown actually.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14460316" author="tug" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2004 16:14:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here you go:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a = new Object()&lt;br/&gt;
a.missingmethod()&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14460293" author="guillaume" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2004 05:37:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed, MissingMethodExceptions were caught even if it wasn&apos;t with a missing main method&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
